content.detailedDescription:
Three of us were watching the sunday late nfl game on my neighbor's outdoor tv.  it was the night of the lunar eclipse or super moon.  around 21:13 cst i was watching the moon and then from the south east which is the same angle the moon was at i noticed this red/orange object was traveling towards us.  i yelled, "what the heck is that"?  my two buddies got up and they did not know either.  it had a shape of a rugby ball on it's nose and engulfed in fire or plasma.  it slowed down and then stopped for a second and then turned and headed due north and then it was gone.

the object was probably 1000 to 1500 feet high and did not make any noise what so ever.  all three of us agreed that what ever it was it appeared to be on fire or at lease we all noticed flames surrounding it.
content.summary: It was during the supermoon and we saw what looked like a rugby shaped ball on edge with a red/orange burning plasma or fire all around it. it slowed, then turned north and took off and then it was out of site.

content.detailedDescription: Myself, boyfriend and friend were traveling south on highway 101 headed to coos bay. it was around 4 a.M when we noticed the battery light come on. as we headed south for a few miles, the cars lights and electronics were flashing on and off and as we pulled over near mp 168 and the cars lights and engine died. we couldn't restart the vehicle. we exit the car to see if the battery had a bad connection but finally concluded it was the alternator. we then tried calling for a ride or tow but our cell phones had bad service and were about to die. we didn't know exactly where we were and all of us were very disorientated. we eventually got a call out to someone to come get us from coos bay they were on their way. as i look around the sky had never ever seen the galaxies and constellations so clearly like i had that evening. it was incredible. as i look to the south, my eyes immedeitly went to what i thought was a star. i quickly learned it wasn't a star although it could pose like one. it began to make sudden changes in direction and turn abruptly changing color and altitude unlike any thing i have ever seen. i then noticed other star like crafts maybe 15 through out the sky. they seem to be communication with each other. to my left was a mountain and as i look up i saw a pink like light or flash every so often come from the mountain behind the trees. i then went back to the car to let the others know what i had saw they had seen the same and agreed we were seeing ufos. we sat and watched from the car with no lights and both doors open. both my friend and i could see black/grey looking beings move so fast past us to the back of the car. unafraid i got out of the car and went up as close to the craft as i could for a better look. it was hypnotic the way it moved. my friend got out of the  car and came to where i was observing and took a flashlight and shone it at the craft. as she did the craft was coming closer and closer. i told her to stop and sent her back to the car with my boyfriend who was in denial and terrified. i stood there looking for maybe an hour with no noise from craft and no other vehicles came by. my friend and boyfriend said it didn't move and inch. i had realized i had been hypnotized by the craft. i remember looking down with my eyes and seeing little green beings stacked up in front of me as a flash image. when i physically had looked  down at the beings a voice came through my head saying back up hear meaning  look up at the small craft and i realized we were communicating telepathically. they had told me they had no emotions and were not going to hurt us. they said they were there to help something to do with the ocean. at some point i came out of the hypnotic state and made my way back to the car. at that point we were still all trying to figure out exactly where we were when a hiker appeared and asked if we were okay. i said yes and asked exactly where we were and he pulled out his map and said by mp 168. i made no mention of my experience to him but could still see the craft i had communicated with. i went to point it out to the hiker it changed back into a star. as our ride neared we could actually hear the power being recharged back into our car as if a generator was firing up. then our ride pulled up and we left for coos bay as my boyfriend had to be at work. i have digital pictures and an excellent video i would like to share with mufon not the public at this time.
content.flightPath: Hovering then path,Path with directional change,Path then hovering

content.detailedDescription:
Witnessed at approximately 5:00pm atlantic standard time sept. 27, 2015. fredericton nb canada. 

my wife and i were in out backyard throwing frisbees for our dogs. it was a bright clear fall day with no clouds. there was a lot of air traffic.
2 commercial aircraft were heading west, with one following the other, in a staggered pattern. both aircraft were emitting vapor trails. at a point, approximately 60 degrees vertical from the west horizon, we noticed a third cylindrical object at a 4 o’clock position, behind the first aircraft, following a parallel course heading. it did not emit a vapor trail and had a very reflective surface, which was a lot brighter than the 2 aircraft. this object also appeared to be larger than the 2 aircraft. after watching for approximately 10 seconds it faded and disappeared.

i thought that the object may have been the international space station, which i have witnessed before, so i checked the nasa website to check the orbit schedule. nothing matched up. i then checked the iridium flare satellite schedule and nothing matched up.
we are not sure what we witnessed.
content.summary: Large, reflective, cylinrical object with no vapor trail following commercial aircraft, then disappearing

content.detailedDescription: Dear sir(s) at 8:30 p.M. (per i-phone time) last night (sunday september 27th) my brother and i were outside looking at the stars, the milky way was visible. a light appeared above the horizon coming from the north. at first both of us thought of a satellite or an airline flight from spokane to portland. i see many aircraft both during the day and night heading to or from seattle plus the spokane to portland route. i am also very aware of the c-17's, c-141's, helicopters and agriculture spray planes i see on a daily basis. the object was coming almost straight at us from the north ( i checked with the compass on the i-phone) heading south. my best guess of it's speed was somewhat faster than the satellite( i have observed them going from a west to east direction two different times) and those usually take many seconds (20 to 30?) to move from horizon to horizon and this came at us from the horizon in maybe one second. as to altitude i believe it was below an airline flight (28 to 35 thousand feet). it had no sound as far as we could ascertain. because of the airline flights and military aircraft that land at the airport at moses lake i am aware of both helicopter and jet exhaust sounds so i feel i can safely say that it was neither fixed or rotary winged. at that time the two options (satellite or airplane) were still in both our minds but what really stood out was the right angle turn heading west, (again using the i-phone compass), there was no slow down or arc to this motion, it was instantaneous! the object then headed west in the direction of yakima. now it did a different thing, it slowed so we could see it for maybe one second more as it moved away from us but it must have slowed from it's original very high velocity. it had blinking white lights. a few moments later a blinking light appeared in the east, (toward the tri-cities) and while this was nowhere as fast as the original ufo twice this one moved with the strange changes in direction that seem unlike any vehicle, (air,land or sea) that i have ever seen, apparently without inertia. while in the u.S.A.F. i have worked on both the sr-71 and rf-4c's plus working at boeing for 25 years on 767,747 and 777 airplanes. i also have been a model airplane enthusiast since childhood so i feel i know something about how airplanes behave in flight and i can honestly say that this was unusual to say the least. in total i think there might have been 2 seconds to the whole sighting.
content.summary: White lights blinking, no red or green tip lights moving very fast( much faster than common airliner

content.detailedDescription:
On march 6, 2015 i was traveling east bound on briley pkwy west. it was during thesnow that we had around then, and because it was around 11:30 or 12am and icey i was the only person on the road. as i approached the bend 3/4 of a mile before the whites creek pike exit i saw a single bright light on the right hand side of the road. it was like a spotlight hovering what appeared to be around 30-40 ft off of the ground. i didnt think much about it. as i got closer the light seemed to slowly spin and become 4 white lights of the same brightness. i cant be sure that it spun but i think it did. whatever it did, it became 4 lights. as it did that, it slowly began to move in a straight line across briley pkwy and stopped over a house that is on the left hand side from where i was. it sat there for as long as it took me to drive past, to where it was obscured by trees and the hill that is there. 
before the bend where i lost view is a long straight away about a mile long. i witnessed the light the whole time i was driving down that straight. and because it was icey i was moving pretty slow so i had it in vision for a couple of minutes. as i passed, it was in the air above that house and i rolled my window down to see if i could hear anything but i couldnt. i couldnt see anything the lights were mounted to. it seemed to be about 20-30 feet across. when i came back going the opposite direction about 15 minutes later it was gone. i at first assumed it was a helicopter, but as the other lights appeared it seemed odd. the way it seemed to spin without the first light being affected or dimmed. all the lights seemed to be facing me the whole time i was witnessing it and behind it seemed to be completely black. it creeped me out. i guess it was around 150 yards away at its closest point.
content.summary: Single bright light appeared to spin and become 4 lights of the same brightness. hovering

content.detailedDescription:
My partner and i were outside on the verandah feeding our dog. it was just before dinner time, around 7:30 pm when we heard a short loud indescribable noise. we ran out onto the grass just off the verandah and spotted what appeared to be a falling ball of fire. i initially thought it was flaming debris from someones firecracker, as there is a large field of bushland meters away. however, it appeared to move n-ne in a starlight line, defying cross winds. as it descended slowly towards us, getting bigger and brighter, we could distinctively see the colours of its flames, beating just like a candle and bright yellow. you could begin to hear cracking and popping noises, just as if you were next to a camp fire. it appeared to be right above us just hovering in one place, in what seemed to be minutes passing by. the fireball then started to move in an upward angle, we could feel the heat emanating from it as it began to ascend in a s-sw line. it faded slowly, not like it was going out, but as if it was moving farther away giving a soft orange-red glow, before disappearing from sight. 

i decided to report the incident to the bureau of meteorolgy and the local observatory, and their responses were almost identical. stating that there was a jet demonstration that afternoon where the pilots burned their fuel. they also described in detail what fuel burning is, as if it was definitive that the object was nothing more. 

my upbringing was in a royal air force family, and we see many demonstrations of jet fly-bys and fuel burning, but none that last more than seconds. none that can match the movement or duration of what we had seen that night. 

i am still uncertain of what we had witness that night.
content.flightPath: Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: Fireball in sky, hovered above us and changed direction. dull cracking noises present, gave off heat.

content.detailedDescription: My wife and i were sitting on the back deck with our children watching the supermoon/lunar eclipse.  at 9:43, the kids had just gone inside when my wife and i saw a triangular craft directly in the sight of the moon.  the craft had blue and red lights blinking rapidly, and there were stationary lights shining on the bottom.  while in sight of the moon, the craft maneuvered with 90 degree angles and what seemed like sharp figure 8 motions.  a few seconds after moving sporadically, the craft stabilized and flew in a straight line out of sight.  besides the impressive maneuvering, the triangular craft moved at a rate of speed seeming faster than what a jet would.  the craft looked solid with its triangular shape.

content.detailedDescription:
My girlfriend, my two sons 6 and 11 years old and i were at a friend's birthday bbq. my boys were the only kids there so they were off kinda doing their own thing while the adults all drank some beers and chatted. i'd have to say it was around 2030-2100 that i overheard them talking about ufos and playing with my toby's (he's the 11 year old) phone and looking off to the east of the yard just above a tree line. i figured they were playing and paid it little mind. 

about 5 mins later, toby asked me where he could plug his phone in to look at a picture. we weren't really that familiar with the hosts, so i was hesitant to go looking around for outlets and asked him what picture. he immediately showed me and said that he and his brother just watched a ufo. they said it hovered just above a tree in the neighbor's yard and then shot out of sight right after he took the picture. 

i humored them and did the dad thing, like "oh... yeah? very cool! let me see?" 

when he showed me the picture i immediately changed my tone. i asked him to show me exactly where he was standing and where he was pointing his phone when he took this picture. the area he was pointing it had now street lights in the field of view and i could faintly make out the exact arc of the tree giving a point of reference. you'll notice to the right an arc coming down from the top right corner of the image to about 1/3 of the way across the bottom- this perfectly corresponds with the tree line as seen from the back yard of the host. 

i showed it to some friends at the party and they all kind of dismissed it since it was in fact a party and they had more important discussions and drinking to attend to. 

no one else witnessed this. no one heard anything. as far as i know no one else experienced anything out of the ordinary. 

my boys were excited, and they are very honest with me, objective and always well-behaved. i have no reason to believe they were doing anything but honestly watching a ufo. and the picture, with it's shape and where the image was located... that all gave me chills.

i have no clue what it is, my son took it on his phone. the phone is a samsung galaxy 4 mini. he text me the pic after he took it so i can't account for any resolution loss or image changes in that process. i have no problem allowing access to that phone for the original pic if need be, as long as he gets his phone back in tact. 

thanks for your time, hopefully this will be fun!
content.summary: My 2 sons were talking about ufos at a party, took a picture.

content.detailedDescription:

viewed at middle of lake from private island owned by multimillionaire industrialist. still owned to current date. as actual and true that this report is i am taking over 25 years to report this.Only talked among us three eyewitnesses over the years and family.

now i wish this could end here but it does not. the three of us two female adults and a male decide to leave pantry and go to end of northside island dock with a single beam flashlight.All huddled together under rain or tarp.
suddenly our strange lights fantasy turns to frank reality when we saw an amazing undeniable incident occur. i started flashing the mini flashlight off and on at docks end.Suddenly without warning at incredible speed travelling one mile in a few seconds a huge dark grey half football shaped 
object raised above gull rock responded to our light and in 2 seconds or less was hovering only 100-200 feet tops in front of us at end of dock.Shocking,impossible but yes only 50 75 feet away.Encompassed majority of front of island a football field in length.No noise no hum nothing but huge. no windows no alien things nothing observed.However something responded to our flashlight and was observing us. what now appeared. only at the bottom of this half football dark object clearly visible especially after a flash of intense lighting, was turned on suddenly a series of white,green and red triangular 3 foot rotating sections of bright coloured light spinning slowly.Nothing at top.I continued turning flashlight off while 2 females looked in shock at craft.Then suddenly only left side of craft turned on its mini moon of light and started randomly signaling us for 1 minute.Wife of industrial yelled for me to shut dame flashlight off be we are scared.I shut off flashlight for good. quickly after left mini moon light shut off the craft within 1 minute went back to gull rock in water within 1 second one mile. no noise , no hum nothing.This object 1n 1988 not from this world. after returning to gull rock right left lights of mini moons appeared went 300 ft up and keep crisscrossing lake for 10 minutes.Suddenly mini moons went back to craft at gull rock turned off.Something at a great speed like a flash went to right side of lake behind sparlings island by shallow swamp.Suddenly mini halo .4 of a mileof energy light diminishes until not visible. a rapid flash of light with a reddish trail shots straight up into atmoshere until no longer visible with naked eyes. incredible rate of speed with no noise or sounds. interestngly rain stops and flash lightning clears.Still no electricity on lake or area.
next day observation maybe 2-5 seagulls left on gull rock not usual hundreds.

content.detailedDescription:
Green orb scanned the valley with huge green beam on lunar eclispe night in montana below clouds

this ufo *scanned* the area like something i have never seen before. i have never seen a ufo before and this was one of the craziest things ive ever seen. 

it is the night of the lunar eclipse-the blood moon eclipse that only comes around once every 20 years. i think this has bearing on the sighting. 

i was on my way back from bridger mountain rd. coming back into bozeman, and at exactly 8:40pm on the left in the sky above the tree line but below the total cloud cover was a large green orb hovering. the distance id have to check because it is very hard to tell how far away it was in the dark, but when go back during the day, i will be able to gauge the actual distance. maybe...It was a half mile away. it didnt do anything for about 10 seconds. then like wow...From about a half mile away a beam of green light literally scanned the whole area, but only on the land part. it lasted for about 5 seconds, then stopped for another 3 seconds and scanned the land for another 5 so seconds. as if it was looking for something downed in the area. there is like nothing out were it was scanning, except for forest and maybe a house or two. the scanning beam is freakishly i almost want to say high-tech. from where it was to where it was able to scan was a very large distance, and even the actual beam of light showed almost an electronic pattern. this beam was a concentrated beam like most ufo sightings you hear about, but when it scanned farther from its own distance, the beams range of light pie'd out. this part is hard to explain. im an artist so a drawing would be best. not only did it scan a green light, but when it did, when the green beam was hitting the landscape, it wasnt even like a monotoned green light, it seriously looked like that light was making a design within that beam. like the design a motherboard has for a computer. like it was trying to pick up a computer sequence is the best i can do to explain it. the scanning lite up the whole valley when it happened. remember, it ws cloudy, and no moon and i was in the middle of a forest with very little lighting. after the scanning it there there only for 2 seconds and then gone. there was a car behind me, and they have got to have seen it. i was just amazed at the range this thing had and how it wasnt just a beam scanning, it looked like a computer system trying to locate a chip.
content.summary: Green orb scanned the valley with huge green beam on lunar eclispe night in montana below clouds

content.detailedDescription:
At 8:40 pm, i was watching the blood moon, and when i looked up at the stars i was startled to see 3 lights in a triangle formation, going north. it appeared that they were in orbit above the earth. if satellite travels at 15,000 mph, then these were travelling at twice that speed.
there was no jet noise, no sonic booms. obviously travelling in orbit above earth. there was a great distance between the 3 objects lights that were travelling.
i don't believe in ufos. but i do report what i saw.
content.summary: 3 star like objects, in triangle formation, heading north

content.detailedDescription: My girlfriend was driving on highway 290 passing the mannheim rd exit. the super blood moon was nearing full eclipse at 9:09 pm. she opened the sunroof on the car to take two pictures. she took the pictures and didn't think anything of them. when she picked her other up and returned home, she showed me them. i immediately noticed a horse shoe like object in both pictures. the object is uncharacteristic of any plan that i have ever seen. the horseshoe is made up of 8 spheres that look yellow. 290 and mannheim rd is close to ohare international airport.
content.summary: Taking picture of blood moon out sunroof when a horseshoe object appeared in picture

content.detailedDescription: I was at the beach in dana point viewing the lunar eclipse with my husband and many other dana point residents were there, too.  because we were all looking up to see the moon, we all saw this low hovering formation of nine bright lights.  the lights were in a formation then they moved slowly into a couple different formations--someone said it looked like they were trying to make constellations.  after doing this for a few minutes, they moved off into the distance, into a small cluster.  then they got into a line and eventually were so small they couldn't be seen anymore.  strangest thing i've ever seen.
content.summary: Nine lights in formation hovered then moved away together and disappeared

content.detailedDescription: On 9-27-15 at approximately 9:00 pm while stargazing and watching the lunar eclipse in our backyard, my husband and i witnessed an almost transparent translucent craft with dull blood-orange lights drift above us heading south in a staight line. the craft made no sound. the sky was dark and clear. the sighting lasted about 3-5 seconds before it was out of our sight behind our house. it appeared that the craft was extremely large, but we could not be certain the altitude of the object.  we have never seen anything like this before.
content.summary: My husband and i saw a translucent boomerang craft during the lunar eclipse.

content.detailedDescription: We were waiting for the lunar eclipse to appear and i decided to take some pictures of the crowd gathered along the road. we never saw any lights, etc except for the occasional car lights coming down the mountain. the pictures were taken with a canon t5, f-11, 1/125, timer was set for 2 sec. while going thru the pictures and sharpening them some, i saw these 2 strange shapes along the skyline. the 3rd picture does not show them anymore. i honestly did not see anything but obviously my camera did. my lense is brand new and there isn't any dust on it. i'm gobsmacked!
content.summary: Taking night pictures of mt. hamilton, waiting for lunar eclpse

content.detailedDescription:
Stepped outside to see lunar eclipse, gorgeous night. out of corner of my eye spotted off to my right was an object going south to north in a straight line. what was unusual was that it was all red with like forks or spokes of red with no other colors but red, and this object made no sounds at all. also wasn't that high unlike some planes we saw a little time after which were a lot higher, multiple lights and you could here them. night was perfect, cool, no wind, cloudless.
my wife was with me and observed it all. i video taped it. about a min and 10 sec.

this object just went out of sight, north.
content.summary: Bright red, forks of red, no other colors. silent
